RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAKE NO MISTAKE settled in midfield outside foes three wide on the first bend, improved outside runners down the back straight, cruised to the lead at the three furlong pole, opened up at the top of the lane and held safe by a diminishing margin at the wire. TEMPEREYA was nestled on the rail in the early stages behind the frontrunner, started to reach for more ground shifting outside three wide going around horses at the quarter pole and determinedly chased the winner home closing in smartly at the finish line. ITS A BIRDIE was coaxed early tp get the lead on the rail heading into the first turn, slowed the pace down dictating terms up front down the backstretch, was collared by the winner at the three furlong marker outside, offered no resistance and mildly finished up on the fence down the lane to hold for third money. AMI'S LINK was off a step slow to trail in the early going, travelled outside four deep stalking at the half mile marker, rallied three wide around rivals at the three eighths pole making a brief run and levelled out through the stretch to settle on the fringes in the end. ERASMO'S GIRL stalked between foes having one rival beaten on the first turn, could see the bunched up field at the half, made little headway on the final turn and passed a weary runner in the stretch. THUNDERHEAVYRAIN tracked the pacesetter outside on the first turn, shadowed the leader down the backstretch could not maintain position between runners who were making a move at the seven sixteenths pole and emptied out at the top of the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUGARTAP broke through the gate prior to the start, tracked behind the front pair down the backside, angled out closing in three wide at the quarter pole, pounced to the lead at the furlong marker on just held on running on the wrong lead to the finish line. BUSTA GROOVE was off a step slow to begin, trailing on the fence in the early stages, saved ground at the back around the bend, was looking for room the extend his stride in upper stretch, found a seam for clear run in the four path at the eighth pole and closed in quickly, just missing at the wire while not switching leads through the stretch. AUTUMN'S SO FLASHY was void of speed settling near the back between foes down the backstretch, began to pick up rivals three wide at the quarter pole and finished up gamely between foes in mid-stretch to be a non threatening third crossing the line. CUT'EM LOOSE was slow at the start, stalked on the outside near the rear down the backside, made mild progress three wide through the turn, swung out widest in the six path straightening for the drive and finished with intent for a minor share. COMMANDER AT SEA tracked three wide with runners on each side down the backstretch, was in tight briefly inside the three furlong marker to be shuffled back some on the turn, rallied in the two path in range of the leaders at the top of the stretch, lost his path and momentum at the sixteenth pole and could not recover in time to pose a threat at the finish. LLOYD prompted to pace outside down the backstretch, was nudged for more at the three furlong marker, assumed the lead at the quarter pole, could not find more late and yielded on the fence at the sixteenth pole. IT'S ME MARIO tracked four deep outside rivals in the early going, was scrubbed on keeping pace three wide around the turn, shifted outside in the five path turning for home but had little to show in the drive to the wire. HARD RELOAD took this field on the rail down the back straight, was headed outside with five sixteenths to go, offered little response and backed away through the field on the rail in upper stretch.

JUST FOR MADDIE stalked near the back on the inside under a snug hold, was checked when in tight between runners at the three furlong marker losing momentum and could not recover down the stretch to be a factor. TIMESKIP galloped along tracking the top two between runners down the back straight, moved in closer two wide with rivals on each side midway on the far turn, posed a threat in the four path straightening out for home but did not have enough to go on with the top two finishers in the last few jumps before the wire. OCTOBER FROST travelled in the middle of the pack all alone in the early going, improved down the backstretch four deep outside runners at the half, could not gain four wide around the final turn, shifted outside to the six path in upper stretch and was no menace through the lane. HALF LIT tracked on the rail in the first turn through the backstretch, was urged on the fence at the quarter pole, could not keep pace with others starting to move in upper stretch and faded on the rail at the furlong marker. NATIVE PRINCE tracked the frontrunner on the outside in the early stages of the race, chased the pacesetter at the three eighths pole and was overwhelmed by runners on each side at the quarter pole and emptied out in the stretch.
